article.description: The Big Ten's best defense did its job in Michigan State's 72-47 victory Thursday night over Wisconsin.
article.headline: Spartans' Roehrig scores season-high 19 points
article.linkText: Spartans holds Wisconsin to less than 50 points
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Kelli Roehrig had a season-high 19
points, and the Big Ten's best defense did the rest in 20th-ranked
Michigan State's 72-47 victory Thursday night over Wisconsin.

Victoria Lucas-Perry had 11 points and Patrice McKinney and
Lindsay Bowen 10 apiece for the Spartans (17-4, 7-3).

Ashley Josephson had 17 points and Emily Ashbaugh 10 for the
Badgers (8-12, 2-8), the 10th team to score fewer than 50 points
this season against the Spartans.

Michigan State's matchup zone held Wisconsin to 33-percent
shooting -- including 17 percent from 3-point range. The Spartans
shot 45 percent -- 47 percent from beyond the arc -- and had a 42-32
advantage in rebounds.

Roehrig was 8-for-10 from the field, mostly on putbacks and
passes from Bowen, who had a career-high seven assists.

The win gave the Spartans, upset Sunday by Iowa, three straight
seasons with 17 or more wins for the first time in school history.
